wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
ladies, strong women don’t play victim or make themselves helpless. they stand up and fight. 
i am so stoked about the new ongoing women's self defense class @calcourtsfitness with experience trainer jason manki. this class emphasizes reality-based concepts and movements, including mind set training. 
lean how to legit protect yorself, and build your self confidence.
it’s in our nature as women to protect and defend. it’s always the female of the species- the tigris and the lioness in you- that will defend when attacked. .
personal safety should not be assumed! .
join us every saturday, 1-3pm at the annex. bring your friends and daughters. strong women always support other women.  @calcourtsfitness #calcourtsannex #metoo #girlpower #defendyourself #women #womensrights #feminism #strongwomen #womensselfdefense

text:
in the last installment of our series how we'll win, we spoke to 50 men about what it means to be a man, a feminist, and an ally and one thing is certain — men must put in the work for change to happen.

one example is alexis ohanian, co-founder of reddit and initialized capital, who shared with quartz what he's doing to advance gender equality and the important lessons he took away from the #metoo movement.

from leaders such as senator @corybooker to @harrys ceo andy katz-mayfield, these men shared powerful insights on how to work towards gender equality and how we can all inspire change. 🙌🏻#howwellwin #theotherhalf #equality #metoo

be your own badass in 2019. 
_____
posted @withrepost • @tufflovefitnesscollective women’s self-defense workshop💪🏼
____
in self-defense, we advocate to first practice awareness strategies, de-escalate, distract and escape. but if that’s not possible, we teach how to use the principal of leverage to multiply the force on your attackers and how to use their biomechanics against them. for example, make their elbow joint go in a direction it is designed not to go. this technique is called the arm bar. it can be used when someone is in between your legs.
______
our self-defense workshops welcome female ages 9+. no experience necessary. deets below:

registration: you may pay at the door or reserve your spot by clicking the link at our bio.

text:
💫аукцион завершён💫
⠀ 
объявляю аукцион! на кону бортик косичка как на фото👆🏼
🌸из 3-х звеньев нежной бело-розовой расцветки
🌸сшита из хлопкового велюра, внутри гипоаллергенный наполнитель холлофайбер, поэтому бортик безопасен даже для самых маленьких👼🏻
🌸высота косички около 17 см, поэтому вы без труда будете наблюдать за малышом, а он за вами👀
🌸длина 3,3м (подойдёт на весь периметр прямоугольной и овальную кроватку, а еще можно использовать в подростковой кроватке😉)
⠀
✅начальная ставка 900₽;
✅шаг 100₽.
✅доставка почтой рф за счёт победителя 350₽
✅аукцион завершается спустя сутки, после последнего повышения ставки, или спустя сутки, после публикации, если ставки отсутствуют
✅победителем станет тот, кто оставит последний комментарий со  ставкой.
.
‼️важно‼️если вы не готовы гарантировать выкуп лота в течение 2-х дней после завершения аукциона, прошу воздержаться от участия!

text:
for years i had worked out and watched what i ate yet gained weight because i could not stop binge drinking and overeating and missing workouts. it wasn't all the time and everyone else in treatment had suffered far more serious consequences to their lives than i had but i was totally addicted just like everyone else. i was just fortunate to have a work from home job, flexible career and don't drive often so i avoided those issues 
to improve my wellness i took a step that is relatively rare and got help before things got that bad and used my insurance benefits to create the type of recovery that best suited me. for me it meant going to malibu and uncovering the underlying issues that were driving the drinking in the first place and letting go of the pain from the past. i implemented sobriety like i implement software, with a phased and focused approach to create a better life for myself. i set goals and various deliverables for myself to ensure that i was seeing the benefit of the changes i was making. when you get treatment early in the progression of the issue you have the ability to enjoy the process, rather than look at treatment as something to be ashamed of i treated it like a wellness retreat with a focus on addiction and applied the information to all the addictions in my life like overspending, online dating and sugar. i didn't lose my job, instead i got promoted the year i came back. i saved money in the process and paid off all my debt. we can recover and create new lives, the first step is getting the right help before things get out of control. we don't have to believe the narrative that recovery is painful, my recovery was the opposite. it's been the most fun and interesting experience of my life 💓 let's end the stigma attached to alcoholics and substance abuse in our country so no one feels ashamed of getting help 💓

thoughts on the #metoo movement. .
i wonder if it would have been possible without the internet. if we were relying on mainstream media to get these stories out, i doubt many of them would see the light of day. how many brave souls that can broadcast their stories out to the world now would have gotten shut down by their peers in the past behind closed doors.
.
as we become more connected, we expose the dark side of our humanity. the ideals of culture no longer define our society, because through the handheld supercomputers we come to know the truth about one another.
.
i do not believe we are regressing as a society, nor do i believe that violence, sexual or otherwise, occurred less in generations past. .
it simply wasnt included in the historical record. .
now we write the history, and the way society will progress morally is through honest conversations with those who are oppressed or victimized. the coming generations need to hear the stories and see justice served.
.

#abstract #splatter #makearteveryday #imakeart #culture #thoughts #rants #chill #friday #artistsofinsta

text:
die entscheidende ursache, warum die generation y, zu der ich auch gehöre, weniger real hat als vorherige generationen wird leider verschwiegen: der staat als räuber über steuern und sozialbeiträge. zahlte ein arbeitnehmer 1970 noch 13,25% seines bruttolohns ins die sozialkassen, sind es heute bereits über 20%.
hinzu kommen eine um 8 prozentpunkte (ermäßigter satz 1,5%) höhere umsatzsteuer seit 1970, die einführung verschiedener verbrauchssteuern und umlagen/umlagefähige steuern wie z.b. mineralölsteuer, ökoumlagen beim strom, grundsteuern, die auf die mirtnebenkosten umgelegt werden etc. abgesehen davon ist die kalte progression nicht in dem maße abgemildert worden wie löhne gestiegen sind, sodass heute durchschnittlich ein höherer anteil den einkommens über die einkommensteuer verloren geht.
erschreckend eigentlich, dass die generation y nicht auf die barrikaden geht, und weiterhin parteien wählt, die die steuern noch weiter erhöhen will, statt zu senken. kulturmarxistische indoktrination sei sei dank.
.
.
.
.

text:
meet our director, francesca di cesare! @fdcinnyc "i’ve been developing new work for a good few years now, and what i love about it is having the opportunity to help shape and build characters, learning about their story and why it’s important as you go along. i started working on scar tissue about 18 months ago, and upon my first reading i found myself nodding along to it - this story speaks the truth of so many, if not all, women. in a year when women are speaking out, coming forward and supporting each other, this play is more relevant and more crucial to the conversation than ever. and that’s what my vision is, to be part of the conversation. not to make a judgement, but to share in telling our story. scar tissue is the bravest piece of theatre i’ve ever worked on, and i’m honored to be a part of it. #metoo #timesup
.

.

text:
in ireland, a 17 year old girl was raped by a 27 year old man. the man walked free because the girl was wearing a thong. the judge forced her to hold up her underwear in court and that was used as proof that it was the girl’s fault, not the man’s. the girl killed herself shortly after. this is not okay. we need to end victim blaming and start blaming the perpetrators. and, the man wouldn’t have even seen her underwear until he had already undressed her. it’s disgusting that this is considered acceptable in today’s society
• • •

text:
oasis

you are water & i am sand

you are steam & i’m a wrinkle

you are ice & i am butter

you’re the wind against my shutter

i am silver & you are gold

i have secrets & you’ve been told

i am cracked & you the glue

you’re a path of only two

i was the student when you were the teacher

now i’m the professor & you the apt pupil
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
✨i think saying “me too” can be a powerful way to let others know they are not alone. many people carry shame about parts of their lives—a divorce, losing a job, not working out, having a miscarriage, cutting cut from a team...the list is endless •
now imagine: whatever you carry shame around...what if someone said, “me too.” you’d instantly feel a little less shame because you’re not the only one & suddenly you open up a conversation rich with connection 💕
•
be brave & find ways to share your “me too” with people in moments of struggle #metoo#empathy#compassion 💕
•

text:
[le #vendredilecture de la féministhèque 📚🌺] qui dit vendredi dit #vendredilecture ! cette semaine on va causer sexisme à hollywood avec l'ouvrage "brave" de @rosemcgowan ("debout" pour l'édition française) ✊🏻🔥 merci à la @librairiegalignani pour son généreux don 👑

rose mcgowan, c'est l'actrice badass qu'on a vu dans des films cultes tels que jawbreaker, planet terror, ou encore dans la série charmed et puis... plus vraiment après. et on comprend enfin pourquoi. aujourd'hui activiste, réalisatrice et musicienne, elle a été l'une des premières (et nombreuses) femmes à dénoncer le producteur / porc harvey weinstein #metoo 🐷

elle nous livre ici les coulisses d'hollywoood, qu'elle qualifie de "plus grosse secte de toutes", elle qui a échappé à une autre secte dans son enfance, a subi des violences psychologiques et sexuelles de trop d'hommes, de son père à ses petits-amis à ses collègues à des inconnus dans la rue... elle a également fait un passage en hôpital psychiatrique et dormi dans la rue mineure. on vous prévient, le livre contient plusieurs passages très durs (mais pas de panique, un post-it glissé dans l'ouvrage vous indiquera les pages concernées 🌼) ce qu'on retient de ce livre ? une irrépressible, une grandissante, une saine colère.

in collaboration with the photographer praveen kumar (@catch_me_if_u_can_pk)

poem | sara ali (@sara_asfiyali) | the photo cabinet-6 | 'wake up, my friend'

today you woke up to the world
scrolling down through your facebook feed
deteriorating indo pak relationships, 
syrian child's face soaked in blood and white, 
trump's new sexist statement, 
a new #metoo call out, 
deep-veer wedding picture, 
pm modi's japan trip, 
a jawan killed. 
it's a bad, mad world indeed.
.
then you woke up to a million thoughts, 
electricity bill, house rent, 
deadlines, and dead ends. 
your son's five-figure school fees, 
your wrinkling mother 
whom you haven't visited ever since, 
chapters to finish, 
the report card hid under the bedsheets, 
the greying hair and the dark circles, so deep.
.
and you rushed down the old building, 
squeezed yourself through the busy street, 
you fought the cold wind, 
gasped for air in the crowded bus, 
reached your holy grail, 
ate cold food, abused a few, 
and got abused too, 
heard your mum complain about you
to the neighbour next door, 
and finally, you escaped reality, 
hit the bed and found your peace.
.
but then a thought woke you up again 
when you realized that
today you forgot to breathe. 
the same feeble voice asked you again 
like it did last night and every day before it. 
where are you going, my friend?
name: S A R A • A L I

text:
bei diesen fotos geht es nicht um die architektur der gebäude von las vegas, sondern die verfassung der menschen darin. wer ist stabil genug, wer fällt, wer stürzt ab? der fotograf hunter barnes macht sich in der stadt der spielenden auf die suche nach der körperlichen härte. das alte las vegas wird gefeiert, das aus einer zeit weit vor #metoo zu sein scheint und nicht verschwinden kann – oder nicht untergehen darf.

im buch "off the strip", das bei @reelartpress erschienen ist, kommen sie noch einmal zusammen: die frauen halb nackt, die männer in machoposen, immer mit dem kalten stolz der halbwelt. sie inhalieren alles ganz tief und verströmen die traurige wahrheit vom lebenden klischee in ihren psychostrips. #reelartpress #lasvegas #people #portrait #portraitphotography #vivalasvegas #offthestrip #body #bodypositive #psycho #fashion #harshtruthofthecameraeye #hunterbarnes #oldschool #traditional #rules #outsider #outcast #underdog #demimonde #gambling #apocalypse #men #women #gender #roles

text:
so you think suicide is selfish.... that's one way of looking at it. 
let me tell you what i think suicide is.... suicide is the end of a torturous war with a demon you never invited into your life. a demon constantly gnawing away at everything positive in your brain till it's nothing more than a negative decaying wasteland; convincing you that the people you love don't actually care about you. see, suicide is a master manipulator that can twist any logic you have to convince you that not only will you never be loved, but also, that you are not worthy of even obtaining love. even by those you logically know care about you.

suicide is the demon that sits on your chest, making every breath more painful than the last. before my eyes have even opened, his icy grip starts tighting around my lungs; clenching harder with every breath. his voice reminding me that i don't deserve to be waking to greet another day. and thus begins my daily morning battle to see if i will even get out of bed. 
suicide is the 3am anxiety attacks because of something that i said this afternoon/yesterday/last month. suicide is there belittling every word i say, convincing me that the words i speak are stupid, pointless, and not worth being spoken. 
suicide is driving around aimlessly, praying that someone will cross that yellow line and do what i don't have the courage to. suicide is going on vacation and praying the plane will crash. suicide is walking down the street hoping with everything i have that a transport/pickup/ motorcycle or anything else would lose control and take me out. suicide is going for a hike in the bush late at night alone, because being attacked by an animal is no where near as scary as.....continued in comments ⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️ #suicide #suicidal #suicidalthoughts #suicidalideations #fightingsuicide #fightingthestigma #ridewithrobbie #stigmafighter #stopthestigma #stoptheshame #livingwithmentalillness #bipolar #rapidcycling #mixedstates #ptsd #depression #anxiety #metoo #blogger #blogging #mentalhealthblogger #sicknotweak #mentalillness #bethechange #itstartswithyou #itstartswithme

text:
🌟instagram выпустил обзор тенденций платформы за 2018 год: чем жило сообщество социальной сети в уходящем году.
⠀
💕самым популярным стикером в stories стал heart love от arata, а самым часто используемым фильтром для лица — heart eyes.
❤️в ленте эмодзи «сердце» встречалось в комментариях более 14 миллиардов раз.
🙂самым счастливым местом на земле признан disneyland в токио.
⠀
💥что касается интересов аудитории, то в этом году продолжали расти в популярности фото и видео, которые вызывают приятные до мурашек ощущения (asmr): например, резка мыла.
⠀
💫в игре fortnite также наблюдается взрывной рост: #fortnite — очень быстро набирающий популярность хэштег. крупнейший конкурс вирусного танца года также проходил в instagram — это #inmyfeelingschallenge.
⠀
💬миллионы людей использовали instagram для того, чтобы их голоса были услышаны. основными пропагандистскими хэштегами года были #metoo (1,5 миллиона), #timesup (597k), #marchforourlives (562k).
это демонстрирует, что instagram можно использовать для того, чтобы высказать свою точку зрения на важные вещи🙌.

text:
ariella wolens, writer and curator chooses betty tompkins show “will she ever shut up” as a stand out exhibit in 2018 -closes tomorrow!

in a year that was plagued by the unearthing of staggering cases of brutality against women, it is fortifying to see someone make great art of great pain. betty tompkins—a renegade figure who has been challenging the definitions of what constitutes feminist art since the sixties—presented will she ever shut up?, a new body of work at ppow this year in which she appropriated the trite apologies of some of #metoo’s chief offenders and then painted these guilty pleas upon the bodies of female figures from some of art history’s most beloved images. @bettytompkinsart @ariellawolens @garage_magazine 👊🏼
name: P.P.O.W

text:
full moon 0* of cancer

the cancer full moon is extra significant this year, as it is sets off a string of cancer eclipses coming in 2019.. foretelling the energy of 2019. the divine feminine rising, emotional health, healing, intuition, and embodiment. 
the final full moon of 2018 will rise the morning of december 22nd at 0* of cancer. 
it will just so happen to fall in line just one day after the sun moves into the capricorn constellation at 5:23 pm est welcoming in capricorn season and the winter solstice. 
this energy paints a beautiful portrait of the past year. winter solstice representing the death of the year, at the darkest point of the year contrasts the big, bright new begining the cancer full moon will bring the following morning. the darkest before the dawn. together we rise.

a zero degree moon means its a blank slate. new start. fresh beginning. the zero degree moon also happens to conjunct the newly progressed karmic node in cancer, representing the collective rising of the divine feminine.

this energy alone can summon up the deep hurts, pain, and trauma’s that surged up over 2018 with expansive jupiter magnifying scorpio, resulting in the #metoo movement and the kavanaugh case. there is a level of collective hurt and release needed for us all. look to your chart to see where cancer is in your natal chart to get a deeper understanding how it might be effecting you as an individual.
what you can expect and how to interpret the coming lunar vibes below.

cancer represents the mother archetype of the zodiac. the moon is the natural ruler for the watery sign of cancer, so there is a sense of receptivity and harmony between each other. moon in cancer illicits a sense of home and the mother. it’s time to come home, to yourself, to your truth, to your hearth. come home wild one.  those with their moon is in cancer tend to have strong emotions and perceive the world around them through their feelings rather than intellect. however, because cancers (the crab) may not openly show their feelings drawing into their shell/home, and it’s sometimes difficult for others to figure out where they stand with with this information.
see below for more
name: Lauren Burba ✨🐺

text:
who wears glasses? 🙋🏼‍♀️ who can’t wear contacts bc her eyes 👀 dry out?😢🙋🏼‍♀️
who’s too chicken 🐓 and cheap 🤑 to do lasik? 🤦🏼‍♀️🙋🏼‍♀️
sooo... i’ve been through a lot over my short 36 🙈 years on earth. if you’ve known me for a while this might sound familiar, but just hang in there it’ll be worth it. - 
i’ve had my parents divorce, my father die, no siblings, not really any family in this country, and so that has shaped me in numerous ways. i was ok as a preteen being a “nerd” or “different” but then i got into a relationship in high school that has really messed with my head and self confidence since then. (side note: not my husband bc he’s the bomb 💥 and i’m sooo lucky to have him constantly in my corner!) - 
so it’s taken me a really long time to become ok with myself and being different again. so...... the point:  i’m super excited about my new glasses!! 👓🤩🙌🏼😍🎉🤗 i mean if you gotta wear them, then make a statement! -
be you! 😘 you were made different for a reason and who wants to be the same anyway!?🤷🏼‍♀️ -
do you love them? hate them? how many pairs do you think i have?!🤣

text:
“the aftermath of sexual harassment and/or assault remains in the mind and bodies of victims long after the traumatic events, or series of events occur. all too often, women who report sexual misconduct in the workplace (or elsewhere) suffer silently and alone as they grapple not only with their own trauma, but with the swift backlash and harsh judgements of others. victims exist in a system and a society that often assumes they are not being truthful. a society that prioritizes the ignorant comfort of the status quo and the financial security and reputation of the perpetrators. 
we need to do better. not only do we need to work harder to create safe places of employment, we need to draw hard lines to condemn and swiftly reprimand unacceptable behaviour, and we need to purposely support victims and survivors in the aftermath of traumatic events. this is where you come in.” @mmmarywood and @knymz 
please donate and please share

text:
as you gather with family & friends in the next week, be reminded and encouraged- you may have friends & family members dealing with abuse silently. in conversations, keep in mind many survivors identify with the men and women that have come forward this year.
. . .

whatever your opinion of public figures in politics, the supreme court, usa gymnastics, the catholic church, or the accused- make your home and your presence a safe place. not just for adults but for the little ears that may be listening as well. welcome conversations that may arise.
. . .

survivors, old and young, known and not realized, male and female, are watching and listening. use this special season to affirm the worth that we are all made in the image of god. and that your home, where you gather, and your family are all safe places.
. . .

if you share vocally that you do not believe a survivor, bc of politics, fame, or financial reasons, or the amount of time that’s passed-a family member with abuse in their past may identify your doubt with their experience & internalize it. they will believe you doubt them as well.
. . .

abuse does not discriminate when it comes to political party, age, gender, education level, or religion. i hope you all have a merry christmas and find safe havens among friends and family during this very special season.
.
#metoo #churchtoo #instagramadvantage #tilinsiders #risingtidesociety #thatsdarling #followertofan #followertofansociety

text:
fated karmic twinflame relationship example

december 21, 2018👉swipe for synastry chart

the co-stars of the tv show, "bull," michael weatherly and eliza dushku, are an example of a platonic fated karmic twinflames. i have analyzed both of their dates, times and locations of birth to create a brief sample of their astro synastry chart & report. these two were involved in a sexual harassment lawsuit. his planets are on the left and her planets are in the right. the angle between the planets is in the middle. 
michael 7/8/68♋  eliza 12/30/80♑

saturn conjunct anti-vertex=fated & karmic
saturn square mars=power struggle
mars square saturn=power struggle
pluto square venus=obsession
venus square pluto=obsession
saturn opposite moon=disrespectful
moon conjunct neptune=creative connection
sun square pluto=twinflames
neptune conjunct descendant=delusional
chiron square midheaven=damaged career/public image
chiron square sun=bruised ego
sun square saturn=criticism

his sun is square her pluto. this is a twinflame synastry aspect. platonic and romantic twinflames transform each other. the pluto person tries to profoundly change the sun and the sun resists. she tried to get him to see how wrong his behavior was. instead of changing for the better, he got her fired. also, their sexual harassment lawsuit played out in the public hence the chiron square mc, or midheaven, aspect. chiron is an asteroid known as the wounded healer and the midheaven is our 10th house of career/public image in our natal chart. chiron can heal or hurt depending on the aspect and the free will of the chiron person. this is also a karmic relationship because his saturn is conjunct her anti-vertex. saturn is the bringer of karma. this is a karmic bond from a past life relationship.

text:
i was raped from 2013-2016. prior to that trauma, i encountered a child molester who slipped through the system and subbed for my fourth grade class. i have bits of my memory trying to work out the details but every time i do, i dissociate. god, buddha, the universe, whoever it is out there thank you for protecting me. there’s a lot about my childhood i don’t recall. i’m so grateful. the things that i did experience in my past relationship (2013-2016) were not healthy. it wasn’t love. if i didn’t have my best friend there for me idk what would’ve happened. she was the first person to believe me. one night i pretended to pass out after one of his shows to see what would happen and sure enough he began to maneuver my body into the perfect position to stick himself inside of me. 
i don’t want your sympathy. in fact, if you’re going to take anything from this post it’s that i’m chingona and nobodies ever going to fuck me against my own will ever again. #metoo #maschingona #satx #believewomen

text:
the bart & fleming podcast: takeaways from the year in the movie biz
#best of 2018 #breaking news #podcast #the bart & fleming podcast
the bart & fleming podcast: 2018 in the movie biz | deadline click to skip ad closing in... you will be redirected back to your article in seconds  deadline in the latest episode of the bart & fleming podcast, we look back on the year in the movie business, and what it means going forward. led by netflix, 2018 saw more money and attention spent on films meant not for theatrical release but home viewing. the ground continues to shift, with the aftermath still to be felt from giant hollywood deals fusing disney to fox and at&t to time warner. there were also ripples from the #metoo movement that gobsmacked hollywood and left many of its biggest titans disgraced and gone. the impact has spurred a surge toward inclusion, and creative boundaries that are still shifting. we also discuss the movie hits and misses of 2018, and our own favorites of the awards season. listen here:

text:
#24speciesofcrane day 12, big delays between posts, i will explain my greater than 12hr gap below. #cranespeopletoo

today we were watching @cnn, at the local #vegan restaurant @joebeefmtl with close personal friend and #veganwarrior @cameronrhanes who eats vegan despite running so much that he can barely pronounce it. as i have no television in my home due to acute electromagnetic radiation sensitivity, this knowledge overload was a medium rare ish treat. the anchorperson stated that many ignorant people just wouldnt listen to @presidentdonaldtrump and the @republicanparty and denied funding of the great wall of texas which is proposed to help cut down on high fence hunting and illegal immigrant interactions, yet increase tourism. get your facts right and check them twice dear public! the people in public office got there for good reason, so just listen to them.

for this exact reason, we at #cranequarters put hours of research into each feature crane biopic. we have more texts on cranes than the #bcpubliclibraries and @ubc combined. the grus paleogrus #selfy above also shows an #oilrig barge crane, uncommon in most city harbors these days. this photo is an example of why it is so critical to set the record straight like @hillaryclinton did on the email thing, afterwhich it just blew over due to the overwhelming facts. this poor beast is extinct throughout eastern europe, south and north america. it also is suspected to have vanished from the indian subcontinent. without this crane, migration of humans would be much more difficult. the #mission must go on througout the developing world!

text:
“drowning” a self portrait photo project that is very vulnerable for me. you can read what i wrote & see the rest of the photos in the link on my profile. “drowning” is a very short article and photo series i wrote to portray feelings and moments i have experienced as a sexual assault & abusive relationship survivor with ptsd to bring awareness during the holidays, being that i feel that’s when these issues need light shed on them the most. 
side note, these were all taken on my iphone. i obviously wasn’t taking my canon in the shower lol. as a photographer without the money to upgrade i try to remind others you can be creative with what you have. the best camera is the one you have with you ❤️ #mentalhealthawareness #ptsdrecovery #sexualassaultsurvivor #metoo #ptsdsurvivor

text:
#fbf to when the journey started a year ago to last week when we got into our fifth festival with this little film that could. so proud of @thegreatkatstache and couldn’t have said it better !! #womeninfilm #siblingteamwork #collabtodeath
・・・
almost a full year since shooting this, and i’m so grateful that it has been involved with 5 different festivals, including 2 that are international, as well as 2 just this month!!! always baffled, and always honored. hoping for more, but always growing in the process 🤙🏻💜 this film is supposed to empower victims of all genders, ethnicities, and ages, to show that they are stronger and will continue to grow stronger than any perpetrator. with each voice, the world can be a better place, but only if they’re used. remember to never be silent, and always address these hard, life-changing issues. there is support everywhere you turn, no matter what. #theywill believe you.

text: “restraint means willingly stepping down into the muck and mire of tragedy and suffering so that we may extend help and hope.  it allows us to connect with others, to be a blessing, and to be blessed ourselves.” — dr. diane langberg • to us, this quote is so fitting for christmas, a time we remember the birth of christ, the one who truly entered the muck + mire of tragedy + suffering, extending help + hope • as nuns, his example of giving is not only what inspires us to a dedicated life, but specifically a life of giving to vulnerable women • those who have lived through the muck + mire of any abuse need hope, help, love, + care, + need the space + understanding to heal • it is this work that has connected us to so many people, + through this work we are ourselves infinitely blessed • merry christmas from white field farm!

text:
9 and 1/2 years ago, i was diagnosed with ptsd - post traumatic stress disorder, and i dove into learning all about it. 💖
.
ptsd is unlike any other mental illness because it is not a chemical imbalance the person is born with. it manifests after significant trauma. the trauma can be a major event, or it can come as a result of a slow trickle of sustained trauma. 💖
.
ptsd has the tendency to mask itself, being mistaken for other mental illnesses, so it can take time for clinicians to diagnosis. 💖
.
ptsd manifests differently in every person - the manifestation usually being when one is re-traumatized by a trigger similar to the qualifying event, which results in various presentations linked only to the individual. confusing, right? 💖
.
ptsd is not an illness that only affects veterans. it affects victims of child abuse, sexual assault, battered partners, accidents, natural disasters, ... you name the trauma, and it could be a qualifying event. 💖
.
most importantly - ptsd does not have to be your forever! 💖
.
research and a lot of personal consistent effort turned me into a person who now has ptg - post traumatic growth. 💖
.
up to 1/3rd of people diagnosed with ptsd improve symptoms and report ptg. it takes effort, patience, therapy, medical attention, a support system, and belief in yourself. 💖
.
i believe through education and advocacy it can be more than 1/3rd of people evolving to ptg. i want emotional freedom for all people diagnosed with ptsd. i see you. i am you. i’m here for you. we’ve got this! 💖
.
you can read about my qualifying event titled #metoo at: deconstructingdisorders.com 💖
.
l💡ght & l💙ve
.

text:
😃flashback fridaaaay!!
let’s take it back to atlanta’s finest misses officer 😆 •
🗣”i never imagined i would have embarked on a path in law enforcement. i actually used to get annoyed when people would assume i was going to be a cop after college, when they learned of my criminal justice major. 🙄 
i would always respond “no, you don’t need a degree for that”🤦🏾‍♀️ and then inform them of my intention on being an investigator or attending law school. 
this pic was early 2000’s at my police academy graduation. i got to have a perspective from both sides that most don’t get to experience. looking back i appreciate that time and all the ups and downs. they tried to intimidate me, they lied on me, they blackballed me, they harassed me, they tried to break me, but i survived & thrived! it all led to me being right where i am now, fighting to change tradition and status quo when female protection/safety is concerned! empowering, educating, sharing, and saving you is the mission! “
-tonda
•

text:
#guilt  is a short film about rape culture and toxic social constructions, inspired by the many #metoo and #whyididntreport stories from the past couple of years. it brings up questions as ‘who is  believed in a he-said-she-said-situation?’ ‘what makes a victim?’ ‘where does the line go between self-defense and excessive use of force?’
the movie might not answer these questions, but it is written to be a conversation starter. it is set during the aftermath of the assault and will focus on the emotional damage rather than physical violence. #femalefilmmakerfriday

we all recognise the importance of continuing to strive towards equality in the workplace. however, there is still a long way to go. in light of the frightening information being shared through campaigns such as #metoo and #timesup we need to give serious consideration to how we better support the safety, wellbeing and growth of women in all workplaces.

created in response to feedback from thousands of female leaders, accord provides a simple, cost effective way for organisations to increase trust and engagement, create connections across various levels and provide a structured environment to nurture and develop female talent. importantly, accord represents an agreement between organisations and their female staff to work together to create a safer, more supportive and more equitable working environment.​ #metoo #leadership #femaleleaders #investment #womenleaders #workplaceleadership

text:
hello! my name is ellinor skeppström. i’m a filmmaker and director, currently enrolled at the new york film academy and this is my thesis film. i’ve been creating videos for over 10 years and spent my last 4 years in marketing as a producer and editor at sweden’s leading streaming service.
in my teens, i wanted to become a lawyer, specifically working to help victims of sexual assault. graduating from an economics and law gymnasium program in stockholm, i wrote my thesis about the low rate of convictions of sexual assault. the study was made through an extensive amount of reading, as well as interviews with the police, a criminal professor and a victim.
the survivor's words stayed with me. this is not her story, although it is for her, and every single person that have been harassed, assaulted, shamed, guilted. #femalefilmmakerfriday #metoo

text:
2018 adalah tahun dengan berbagai skandal di k-entertainment dengan banyak masalah kontroversial, tuntutan hukum, dan banyak lagi. sekarang dengan hanya beberapa minggu tersisa di tahun ini, wartawan dari sports today menyimpulkan orang-orang terburuk dengan kontroversi terburuk pada tahun 2018. siapa yang menurut para wartawan adalah yang terburuk tahun ini? lihatlah daftar di bawah ini:
.
1. yang hyun suk: pembatalan debut 'mixnine'
.
"dengan kekuatan yg sebagai agensi, dia mengatakan dia akan membuat debut dan menempatkan peserta pelatihan dalam kompetisi, tetapi membatalkan debut mereka karena program itu gagal. dia menciptakan kontroversi dengan menanggapi geliat terakhir mereka mengambil tindakan hukum dengan gugatan balik. kemudian bahkan setahun kemudian, dia menciptakan acara audisi yang sama 'yg treasure box.' ide ironisnya mengejutkan semua orang. " - reporter yoon hye young.
.
2. lee seo won: pelecehan seksual
.
"tingkah lakunya yang berani setelah pelecehan seksual, ketidaktahuan terus-menerus, dan terakhir, tindakan melarikan diri ke militer. aku terkejut 3 kali." - reporter kim sat byul
.
3. kim saeng min: #metoo
.
"dia menghabiskan waktu emas yang ditunggu-tunggu dalam 25 tahun. kamu mendapatkan apa yang kamu berikan." - reporter kim na yeon
.
4. nancy lang x wang: pernikahan & perceraian yang kontroversial
.
"pembuat masalah dengan perkawinan, perkelahian, dan perceraian yang gaduh." - reporter han ye ji
.
5. lee jin min cp: manipulasi 'heart signal 2'
.
"dia menciptakan program viral 'heart signal' tetapi ada juga banyak kontroversi. dia bahkan lebih mengecewakan penonton dengan perilakunya yang tidak menyenangkan dalam wawancara tentang kesalahan siaran, manipulasi dalam penyuntingan, dan banyak lagi." - reporter moon soo yeon
.
6. microdot: kasus penipuan orang tua
.
"orang tuanya berbohong kepada orang-orang di kota mereka, putranya berbohong kepada pemirsa." - reporter kim hyun min
.
source : @allkpop, oh_mes
trans by : pink

text:
{para reporter memilih 6 kontroversi paling buruk sepanjang tahun 2018}

2018 adalah tahun dengan berbagai skandal di k-entertainment dengan banyak masalah kontroversial, tuntutan hukum, dan banyak lagi. sekarang dengan hanya beberapa minggu tersisa di tahun ini, wartawan dari sports today menyimpulkan orang-orang terburuk dengan kontroversi terburuk pada tahun 2018. siapa yang menurut para wartawan adalah yang terburuk tahun ini? lihatlah daftar di bawah ini:

1. yang hyun suk: pembatalan debut 'mixnine' "dengan kekuatan yg sebagai agensi, dia mengatakan dia akan membuat debut dan menempatkan peserta pelatihan dalam kompetisi, tetapi membatalkan debut mereka karena program itu gagal. dia menciptakan kontroversi dengan menanggapi geliat terakhir mereka mengambil tindakan hukum dengan gugatan balik. kemudian bahkan setahun kemudian, dia menciptakan acara audisi yang sama 'yg treasure box.' ide ironisnya mengejutkan semua orang. " - reporter yoon hye young.

2. lee seo won: pelecehan seksual "tingkah lakunya yang berani setelah pelecehan seksual, ketidaktahuan terus-menerus, dan terakhir, tindakan melarikan diri ke militer. aku terkejut 3 kali." - reporter kim sat byul

3. kim saeng min: #metoo "dia menghabiskan waktu emas yang ditunggu-tunggu dalam 25 tahun. kamu mendapatkan apa yang kamu berikan." - reporter kim na yeon

4. nancy lang x wang: pernikahan dan perceraian yang kontroversial "pembuat masalah dengan perkawinan, perkelahian, dan perceraian yang gaduh." - reporter han ye ji

5. lee jin min cp: manipulasi 'heart signal 2' "dia menciptakan program viral 'heart signal' tetapi ada juga banyak kontroversi. dia bahkan lebih mengecewakan penonton dengan perilakunya yang tidak menyenangkan dalam wawancara tentang kesalahan siaran, manipulasi dalam penyuntingan, dan banyak lagi." - reporter moon soo yeon

6. microdot: kasus lenipuan orang tua "orang tuanya berbohong kepada orang-orang di kota mereka, putranya berbohong kepada pemirsa." - reporter kim hyun min

source : allkpop, oh_mes
trans by : pink
©ksense

2. lee seo won: pelecehan seksual "tingkah lakunya yang berani setelah pelecehan seksual, ketidaktahuan terus-menerus, dan terakhir, tindakan melarikan diri ke militer. aku terkejut 3 kali." - repoer kim sat byul

3. kim saeng min:  "dia menghabiskan waktu emas yang ditunggu-tunggu dalam 25 tahun. kamu mendapatkan apa yang kamu berikan." - repoer kim na yeon

4. cy lang x wang: pernikahan dan perceraian yang kontroversial "pembuat masalah dengan perkawi, perkelahian, dan perceraian yang gaduh." - repoer han ye ji

5. lee jin min cp: manipulasi 'hea signal 2' "dia menciptakan program viral 'hea signal' tetapi ada juga banyak kontroversi. dia bahkan lebih mengecewakan penonton dengan perilakunya yang tidak menyegkan dalam wawancara tentang kesalahan siaran, manipulasi dalam penyuntingan, dan banyak lagi." - repoer moon soo yeon

6. microdot: kasus lenipuan orang tua "orang tuanya berbohong kepada orang-orang di kota mereka, putranya berbohong kepada pemirsa." - repoer kim hyun min

text:
alright so i woke up thinking it would be a great day. but a group of people im close with had a very intense discussion that ended up touching on sexual abuse. and i'll be honest i don't know what hurt worse the reminder of my abuse and breaking down or seeing the entire group breaking down too. it was like.....at first no one was speaking just crying and we all just knew. the pain that shot through the room we knew, we'd all been through abuse of some sort. and while we were all dealing with our own trauma we were supporting each other. and though knowing these people that i think of as family have been through traumatic experiences and it kills me seeing us all support each other the way we did was so beautiful.

text:
esta viñeta de las peruanas alesia lund y eva machado se convirtió esta semana en el símbolo solidario tras el brutal asesinato de la profesora laura luelmo en españa, una de las miles de mujeres víctimas de la violencia machista en el mundo. 
el dibujo de las niñas emma y lola recorrió miles de kilómetros y se convirtió en una de las imágenes más compartidas en internet en el país ibérico, donde ocupó los avatares de miles de personas que buscan visibilizar la lucha diaria de las mujeres que simplemente desean, para el año que viene, volver bien a casa. @emmaylolaperu

text:
for those of you that are a little new around here, here’s a little #fridayintroduction 👋⠀
⠀
i’m chloè and i’m the voice behind the badass boss babe podcast launching on 1/08/19 🍾 ⠀
⠀
here lately, when i haven’t been busting my booty getting ready to launch what’s going to be the best podcast ever you can find me snuggled up in bed with my dog watching satc reruns (i’m a sam/miranda hybrid), drinking too much of @heb’s snickernut coffee on my french press, and planning next year’s programming for my non-profit @girlpowerhoursa. ⠀
⠀
i’m the definition of an extroverted-introvert who’s obsessed with baths, astrology, and goats- in that exact order. ⠀
⠀
i’m passionate about the advancement of women in leadership, which is why i started this podcast.⠀
⠀
that’s me, tell me all about you 💗⠀

text:
2018 adalah tahun dengan berbagai skandal di k-entertainment dengan banyak masalah kontroversial, tuntutan hukum, dan banyak lagi. sekarang dengan hanya beberapa minggu tersisa di tahun ini, wartawan dari sports today menyimpulkan orang-orang terburuk dengan kontroversi terburuk pada tahun 2018. siapa yang menurut para wartawan adalah yang terburuk tahun ini? lihatlah daftar di bawah ini:
.
1. yang hyun suk: pembatalan debut 'mixnine'
.
"dengan kekuatan yg sebagai agensi, dia mengatakan dia akan membuat debut dan menempatkan peserta pelatihan dalam kompetisi, tetapi membatalkan debut mereka karena program itu gagal. dia menciptakan kontroversi dengan menanggapi geliat terakhir mereka mengambil tindakan hukum dengan gugatan balik. kemudian bahkan setahun kemudian, dia menciptakan acara audisi yang sama 'yg treasure box.' ide ironisnya mengejutkan semua orang. " - reporter yoon hye young.
.
2. lee seo won: pelecehan seksual
.
"tingkah lakunya yang berani setelah pelecehan seksual, ketidaktahuan terus-menerus, dan terakhir, tindakan melarikan diri ke militer. aku terkejut 3 kali." - reporter kim sat byul
.
3. kim saeng min: #metoo
.
"dia menghabiskan waktu emas yang ditunggu-tunggu dalam 25 tahun. kamu mendapatkan apa yang kamu berikan." - reporter kim na yeon
.
4. nancy lang x wang: pernikahan dan perceraian yang kontroversial
.
"pembuat masalah dengan perkawinan, perkelahian, dan perceraian yang gaduh." - reporter han ye ji
.
5. lee jin min cp: manipulasi 'heart signal 2'
.
"dia menciptakan program viral 'heart signal' tetapi ada juga banyak kontroversi. dia bahkan lebih mengecewakan penonton dengan perilakunya yang tidak menyenangkan dalam wawancara tentang kesalahan siaran, manipulasi dalam penyuntingan, dan banyak lagi." - reporter moon soo yeon
.
6. microdot: kasus lenipuan orang tua
.
"orang tuanya berbohong kepada orang-orang di kota mereka, putranya berbohong kepada pemirsa." - reporter kim hyun min
.
source : allkpop, oh_mes
trans by : pink
©ksense

text:
yo crearía un nuevo mundo en el que todos conociéramos la vida de los demás, sin tapujos. sus emociones, sus miedos, sus sueños y sus recuerdos.

crearía un mundo en el que no demos por hecho las cosas solo porque las interpretamos así.

muchas personas llevan a diario una careta que muestra seguridad, una armadura que aplaca los golpes por ser extremadamente sensibles y portan todas las herramientas necesarias para que no descubran sus inseguridades.

por favor, vamos a crear un mundo en el que no demos las cosas por sentado, profundicemos en conocer a la gente y desarrollemos la empatía.

quizá estamos perdiendo grandes personas en el camino por no hacerlo.

text:
on july 7 2018 a friend, and former dance teacher disclosed that her boss had raped her. this man is the owner of ottawa pole fitness at 1066 somerset st west. as a student there i was disgusted and never returned. michael hewitt co-owns the studio with his wife li and is also a photographer specializing in boudoir and pole photography. li and michael have tried to sweep this under the rug along with the other instructors. the victim chose not to press charges but did disclose to protect others. i did not make this information public for her protection. but things have changed. i manage business in the same building. i know for a fact li has told her students michael is no longer involved. li has asked her staff and upper students to keep quiet to the lower levels and when my boyfriend confronted both li and michael, michael said he would no longer be around after admitting that he did not fire the survivor but she quit (despite what the studio is saying). michael also said disturbing things like “what do you think i’m going to do, jump out at somebody”, and “this whole me too movement doesn’t even give me a chance” in the words of idris elba “ its only difficult [the me too movement] if you are a man with something to hide”. today, i saw michael helping with renovations. i am uncomfortable with him in my workplace not just for myself but my staff and customers. when my boyfriend asked to speak with him he refused and said he was busy.  when asking a former instructor if he was still not supposed to be involved she snapped back with a lovely “ i don’t know i just teach there ...” after saying she believed the survivor. if you continue to dance there, teach there and give your money to them, you are in fact part of the problem. 
quite frankly i do not care if you are a student there and have a problem with this post. if somebody accused me of something i didn’t do i would be doing a better job of proving my innocence. 
if you condone this kind of cover up you are part of the problem 
screenshot 1-3: the disclosure #metooopf 
#metoo #ottawapolefitness #ottawa #ottawaphotography #michaelhewittphotography #ibelieveher

text:
these.  these little things are adorable and evil at the same time.  you see, i don’t tolerate gluten or dairy well at all, and i often kid myself into thinking just a “few” will be fine. however, the last few days those few haven’t sat well and i found myself needing to sit with my thoughts over it all tonight.
.
.
.
the holidays, and any celebratory days, would be the most intense trigger days for me. i would see these sweets and be unable to take control over my emotions around them. i literally would feel my mouth watering when i’d see them. (seriously...wth?). i would try to ignore them and then literally could not stop thinking about them! i couldn’t even enjoy myself at a gathering until i had one. it’s like a drug.
.
.
it is a drug. sugar affects your brain as fast as cocaine and is just as addictive! did you realize that? it truly has that effect on me even today, which is why i take steps to moderate it. but learning how to do that took some major life experiences.
.
.
i know how you feel when you can’t say no to the sugar. i know how you feel when you have to have one just to feel like you can breathe! it’s embarrassing to be so addicted to something. there’s shame fear, sadness, and depression. then there’s punishment because you can’t believe you’re so weak.
.
.
girl, i get you. i’ve been you. it’s sucks. and it hurts. if this is hitting you right now, let it out - all of it. then know you’re not alone. .
.
breaking the cycle is a 12 week intensive experience where we dive into how you can finally break this hamster wheel of emotional eating. i’m opening registration this week and you’ll get notification if you’re in my list. so let me know if you want on the list, even if just to explore.  you deserve to make 2019 the year you can gain control and freedom over emotional eating. i’ve got you 💕

text:
the beautiful @izumishikawa requested this song for a combo this past fall & when @jennifer_li99 [dancing here] requested a reteach, i couldn’t say no ♥️
-
although i think the intention of the song is that the singer can’t be mad at her person because she loves them so much, i interpreted it as the denial of anger.
of the refusal to call anger by its name.
to suppress it.
-
this theme hit home with me - the idea that anger = bad.
-
i believe that anger is important.
giving ourselves permission to feel angry is important.
why?
because anger tells us that we are afraid of losing something. or that we are grieving. or that we are feeling hurt. it tells us that something happened that matters deeply. & we need to learn to listen to that.
-
i believe anger can be a powerful catalyst for change - in social, political, or personal spheres. it can remind us of our power, our strength, & our capacity to feel big emotions.
-
however, it is also exhausting.
draining.
& while feeling it is important, knowing how to express & process it is even more so. because hurting others, hurting ourselves, pretending like it doesn’t matter, is never okay. ever.
-
we need to give ourselves permission to feel our anger so that we can then do something with it. direct it into positive change. create with it. work through it & release it, so we are free to feel other emotions.
because there are few things more dangerous than untended anger, that simmers beneath the surface for too long.
-
#fridaynightthoughts #boramble
-
thank you @izumishikawa for sharing this song with me - i love & miss you so much! ♥️
thank you @jennifer_li99 for bringing such power, strength, & focus to this movement. i love you so much. ♥️
-
music #madatyou by @noahcyrus

осторожно! градус милоты зашкаливает!это же одна из старших сестричек metoo keppel - девочка-панда!🐼
⠀ ⠀
семейку этих кукол отличают забавные тематические костюмчики, среди которых найдутся нежные коалы, яркие панды, милые конфетки и многие другие.🐾 также куклы представлены в миниформате со специальной петелькой-креплением (высота 22 см), а для особых фанатов найдутся и куклы-рюкзачки.🎒
⠀ ⠀
малышка сделана из высококачественного хлопкового плюша и трикотажа, что позволяет ей также быть отличной сонной игрушкой для вашей крохи. 😴
⠀ ⠀
наполнителем служит превосходный полипропиленовый хлопок, произведенный в южной корее. куколок можно стирать в машинке на деликатном режиме.💦
⠀ 
что ещё делает эту куколку уникальной?
⠀ ⠀ 🎀милые детали: объемная вышивка, воротничок, полосатые чулочки, шапочка с ушками, маленькие туфельки.
⠀ ⠀ 🎀к каждой большой куколке можно подобрать сестричку-малышку, удобную для поездок.
⠀ ⠀ 🎀тематические наряды позволяют окунуться в мир фантазий и подобрать подходящего именно вам персонажа.
⠀ ⠀
высота куколки: 48 см.
⠀ ⠀
для заказа 👉 директ

text: #metoo
name: car car 🦋
tweet_full: #metoo

text:
i am not a big fan of reading newspapers, my main source of news is either tv or family discussion(mostly politics). ok, that’s not even the point. 
today as @himanshu_rajmehta (he reads newspaper while eating) n i were having our breakfast, halfway through he asked me what is going on looking straight at the newspaper n then he finger pointed the news which i read, as i finished reading he finger pointed another than another than another than another. i’ve marked the news below. i didn’t know what to say. after he was done eating he left, but there was a sea of emotions in me which i know i can never express in words. how can someone be so ruthless, so inhuman. for once i just wanted to kill those bastards who had the audacity to rape a 14 years old blind child. yes, she is a child and also a mother now. a 14 year old mother. doesn’t that send chill down your spine.  do you think we as a society are responsible for this? i certainly do. because when a movement like #metoo emerges we are quick to make funny memes out of it, regardless of what those people must have gone through. because we have told our girls it is your attire that is provoking. because we have told our girls come home before ‘o clock after that it is your fault. because we have told our boys ‘it is ok’. well, #itisnotok, it never will be. 
here’s a request to all the young parents out there(i know there are many in my list) teach your boy to respect women(not just their mother or sister, every single one). teach your girls they are equal and should be treated with respect more than anything else. anything less than that, walk away. teach them both the difference between yes and no. what consent is. 
i’ve never been this vocal about my feelings but somethings just need your attention and your voice. ignorance is bliss they say, but not in this case. #speakup #bethechange #educate #womenarenotobjects

text:
there is an amazing portrait artist in belize who has a legit hustle. he carries around a 2’x3’ oil painting of two young sisters. it’s beautiful and sweet and captures a vibrant energy. in viewing the portrait, it’s clear that he understands how to capture his subjects' personalities.
🌴
he also carries around a clipboard and order form, and asks people to commit to his work right then and there... i love his hustle so much. his sales game is inspiring. 🌴
my love and i ran into him one day and decided that we wanted to commission him to paint a portrait of us. we filled out the order form and gave our contact number, but we were not sure what image of us we wanted hanging on our wall. we asked him to be patient... we would know when we had the right image.
🌴
when this picture was taken on our birthday (yes, we share the same birthday) we knew that it was the image we wanted to celebrate every day of the year. to me, it's a reminder to listen to my intuition... when something feels right, i'll know it. 🌴
all of my experiences on the island are based on me paying close attention to my gut because... when you know, you know... and arguing with your soul is a losing battle. embrace your destiny and cherish the beautiful moments that weave the amazing fabric of your story.
🌴

text:
aiming to depict the relatively recent #metoo wave, this piece aims to open up conversations about the movement and all its aspects.

text:
new year resolutions
.
this year has seen the #metoo movement and yes #timesup. if you have faced abuse in any form, please seek help to heal yourself. i know getting professional help is expensive, but you can always talk to your friends if you are comfortable. sometimes getting it out of your system can do wonders.
.
bottling up emotions is never healthy and one day it'll burst. if you can't trust anyone with your vulnerability, write it down. i swear it helps.
.
you don't owe your story to anyone, you do you and take small steps towards being whole again. happiness can only come from within.
.
here's to learning acceptance and unlearning our inherited biases.
.
.
.

text:
title: noni, a little (a lot) tired of the constant harassment she received at pubs and clubs (and it was constant) foisted off her many suitors with a standard, ‘hey, i have to go now, here’s my number... call me’.
jason was one such suitor (harasser) and when he tried to call noni the next day and was met with ‘nah mate, you must have the wrong number’, he exclaimed ‘bitch!’ without so much of a hint of irony that that exact attitude had placed him in that situation in the first place.
noni, an empowered woman of the 21st century continued to lead her life with strength and dignity while jason pissed and moaned on a sub-reddit...

text_retweet:
i echo each and every word out here. #teachyourboys #itisnotok

#repost @gaddedsoul
• • •
i am not a big fan of reading newspapers, my main source of news is either tv or family discussion(mostly politics). ok, that’s not even the point. 
today as @himanshu_rajmehta (he reads newspaper while eating) n i were having our breakfast, halfway through he asked me what is going on looking straight at the newspaper n then he finger pointed the news which i read, as i finished reading he finger pointed another than another than another than another. i’ve marked the news below. i didn’t know what to say. after he was done eating he left, but there was a sea of emotions in me which i know i can never express in words. how can someone be so ruthless, so inhuman. for once i just wanted to kill those bastards who had the audacity to rape a 14 years old blind child. yes, she is a child and also a mother now. a 14 year old mother. doesn’t that send chill down your spine.  do you think we as a society are responsible for this? i certainly do. because when a movement like #metoo emerges we are quick to make funny memes out of it, regardless of what those people must have gone through. because we have told our girls it is your attire that is provoking. because we have told our girls come home before ‘o clock after that it is your fault. because we have told our boys ‘it is ok’. well, #itisnotok, it never will be. 
here’s a request to all the young parents out there(i know there are many in my list) teach your boy to respect women(not just their mother or sister, every single one). teach your girls they are equal and should be treated with respect more than anything else. anything less than that, walk away. teach them both the difference between yes and no. what consent is. 
i’ve never been this vocal about my feelings but somethings just need your attention and your voice. ignorance is bliss they say, but not in this case. #speakup #bethechange #educate #womenarenotobjects

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
vi gör om det (länk i bio):
det här är en sån där på gränsen-text igen. en sån jag vet att folk kommer bli helt bedrövade över och kanske se mig med andra ögon men det senaste året har jag hört så många berättelser från kvinnor på samma tema att jag inte förvånas längre. det finns inget unikt. det är bara helt åt helvete. när berättar man för mycket? finns det något sådant? 
att dela med sig av sånt här är fruktansvärt blottande och det känns som att man balanserar på en tunn tråd för man ger allt av sig själv till en publik man själv inte egentligen bjudit in, jag vet inte vem som kommer ta sig tid att läsa det här. kommer det vara du? hur känner vi varandra? vad kommer du tänka om mig? 
men jag gör det inte för mig tror jag. eller jo, lite. men mest för de som inte har någon röst. som inte vågar eller som inte vill. för mörkertalet. för de som kanske inte överlevde. för de som drabbades så hårt att de har slutat tala. för de som lever i det. vi är många och alla har minnen från olika händelser som samlas under samma rubrik. 
så läs inte för min skull. läs för de andras skull. tänk på att det finns hur många berättelser till som ni aldrig kommer få höra. tänk på oss. på våra förlorade kroppar. på hur trygghet och respekt är två grundstenar i vårt leverne och att vi bör hålla hårt i dessa så länge det går. analysera ditt eget beteende. vänd inte oss ryggen genom att säga att #metoo var överdrivet. för vi finns, det hände oss och nu behöver vi din hjälp.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text: polisen anordnar julfest i linköping, malmö och eskilstuna. och det resulterar i anmälningar om fyra fall av sexuella ofredanden. ett år efter att #metoo briserade. det här gör mig sorgsen. och förbannad. för det krävs mer av poliser. de ska upprätthålla ordningen, se till att andra blir skyddade och möjliggöra bra utredningar som kan leda till åtal och dom. och förebygga brott. när vi, flera tusen kvinnor, beskrev sexuella ofredanden, övergrepp, trakasserier och maktspel inom polisen så slutade vårt upprop #nödvärn med att de samordnande alla tre avgick. anledningen? det gick inte. det gick inte alls att få gehör för vad som framkom. varken verkligt intresse eller engagemang för frågan om utsattheten hos anställda. och det om nåt säger något om en kultur som måste förändras. och det från högsta ledning. för det som förvånar mig är inte att de sexuella ofredandena sker - det är att dom faktiskt anmäls. och det är bra! nu krävs att chefer och ledning tar ett ordentligt tag om en kultur som gör det här möjligt och stöttar alla grymma, fantastiska och engagerade medarbetare som inget annat vill än att göra sitt bästa, både för myndigheten och för allmänheten.

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
instagram выпустил обзор тенденций платформы за 2018 год: чем жило сообщество социальной сети в уходящем году.

самым популярным стикером в stories стал heart love от arata, а самым часто используемым фильтром для лица — heart eyes. в ленте эмодзи «сердце»  встречалось в комментариях более 14 миллиардов раз.

самым счастливым местом на земле признан disneyland в токио.

что касается интересов аудитории, то в этом году продолжали расти в популярности фото и видео, которые вызывают приятные до мурашек ощущения (asmr): например, резка мыла.

в игре fortnite также наблюдается взрывной рост: #fortnite — очень быстро набирающий популярность хэштег. крупнейший конкурс вирусного танца года также проходил в instagram — это #inmyfeelingschallenge.

миллионы людей использовали instagram для того, чтобы их голоса были услышаны. основными пропагандистскими хэштегами года были #metoo (1,5 миллиона), #timesup (597k), #marchforourlives (562k). это демонстрирует, что instagram можно использовать для того, чтобы высказать свою точку зрения на важные вещи.

краткие итоги 2018 года: ▫️наиболее используемый фильтр для лица: heart eyes
▫️самый популярный стикер: heart love от arata
▫️количество комментариев: 14 миллиардов
▫️самое счастливое место в мире: диснейленд токио
▫️главная тенденция: asmr
▫️самый быстрорастущий хэштег: #fortnite
▫️самое топовое сообщество: bts (#btsarmy)
▫️самый популярный челлендж: #inmyfeelingschallenge
▫️топовые пропагандистские хэштеги: #metoo (1,5 миллиона), #timesup (597k), #marchforourlives (562k)
name: Продвижение Инстаграмм

text:
this one is more for the #zgeneration. the #socialmedia addicts and the #facebook friends kinda people. 
in the book of #saintjohn, #jesuschrist is speaking to those who wish to be taught. and in there he says, "this is my commandment, that ye love one another, as i have loved you. greater love hath no man than this, that a man lay down his life for his friends."
most of us don't even have friends we'll talk about life with let alone lay down ours for. we have distanced ourselves from personal relationships and allowed ourselves to devalue what a friend truly means. #friends are people you do anything for. we have become to synnical, that unless your #blood, we don't even care let alone give that creed. since when did we call each other friends just cause we know each other's name? it was never suppose to be like that according to the #scripture. it was suppose to be #loveandhappiness not point and hate. we are allowing the media to distort our image of a #brother and not allowing purity and honestly to drive our inhibitions. when we all see that the only difference between a brother/sister and an enemy is simply the attention given to that person, maybe then we can see that hatred is nothing more than confused admiration.

text: i'm sitting here with tears in my brown eyes and a mind and heart trying to write this tribute to you sisters who still walk this beautiful, horrible world. i want all of you to understand why my tear-stained shirt a hurting sister was forced to sew me is sticking to my soft skin. since this dim, sepia-ish photo was taken by one of my strong mamas on one of the most dazzling days of my life, my eyes are still burning with tears. i'm remembering why my heart that my big sister told me is like a fragile tiffany lamp got broken again. it was 8 days ago that all my mamas and all my sisters told me they were honored hear me recite some of the book of my life. but after they wrapped their arms right around me, held me next to their beautiful broken beating hearts, and cheered me on, i'm still aching for another warm hug from a perfect whole beating strong heart. and i can catch up on the news, but it would burn me like that bright sun and break my heart again. i know far too many sisters of mine out there have been destroyed while i somehow received grace to be loved and tenderly rebuilt. to those sisters: you are the why behind @sistersandheroes. i can't save you, but i can hope to raise my voice and paintbrush and hope, so you will not be a #metoo. so you can always say no. i'll see you on the other side.

text_retweet:
#repost @gaddedsoul (@get_repost)
・・・
i am not a big fan of reading newspapers, my main source of news is either tv or family discussion(mostly politics). ok, that’s not even the point. 
today as @himanshu_rajmehta (he reads newspaper while eating) n i were having our breakfast, halfway through he asked me what is going on looking straight at the newspaper n then he finger pointed the news which i read, as i finished reading he finger pointed another than another than another than another. i’ve marked the news below. i didn’t know what to say. after he was done eating he left, but there was a sea of emotions in me which i know i can never express in words. how can someone be so ruthless, so inhuman. for once i just wanted to kill those bastards who had the audacity to rape a 14 years old blind child. yes, she is a child and also a mother now. a 14 year old mother. doesn’t that send chill down your spine.  do you think we as a society are responsible for this? i certainly do. because when a movement like #metoo emerges we are quick to make funny memes out of it, regardless of what those people must have gone through. because we have told our girls it is your attire that is provoking. because we have told our girls come home before ‘o clock after that it is your fault. because we have told our boys ‘it is ok’. well, #itisnotok, it never will be. 
here’s a request to all the young parents out there(i know there are many in my list) teach your boy to respect women(not just their mother or sister, every single one). teach your girls they are equal and should be treated with respect more than anything else. anything less than that, walk away. teach them both the difference between yes and no. what consent is. 
i’ve never been this vocal about my feelings but somethings just need your attention and your voice. ignorance is bliss they say, but not in this case. #speakup #bethechange #educate #womenarenotobjects

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
lugar mais perigoso para mulheres é a própria casa, diz onu

segundo o relatório, assassinatos cometidos por parceiros ou familiares normalmente não são ataques únicos, mas resultado de abusos domésticos anteriores

londres- o lar é o lugar mais perigoso para uma mulher, indicou estudo da organização das nações unidas (onu) que descobriu que o número de mulheres assassinadas por parceiros ou familiares está crescendo globalmente.

cerca de 50 mil mulheres foram assassinadas em todo o mundo no ano passado por um atual ou ex-parceiro ou por um familiar —  o equivalente a 137 mortes por dia, ou seis por hora —  informou o escritório das nações unidas sobre drogas e crime (unodc, na sigla em inglês). “embora a vasta maioria de vítimas de homicídio seja de homens, as mulheres continuam a pagar o preço mais alto como resultado da desigualdade de gênero, da discriminação e de estereótipos negativos”, disse o diretor-executivo do unodc, yury fedotov, em comunicado.

apesar de recentes campanhas de destaque, como a #metoo, na qual mulheres denunciaram publicamente casos de assédio sexual, elas ainda têm muito mais probabilidade de serem assassinadas por seus parceiros ou familiares.

o número total de assassinatos deste tipo subiu levemente entre 2012 e 2017 –e a proporção de vítimas assassinadas por parceiros ou familiares subiu de menos de meio, em 2012, para quase seis em dez mulheres no ano passado, indicou o estudo.

muitas foram assassinadas por parceiros abusivos, enquanto outras foram vítimas dos chamados crimes de honra ou de disputas por dotes, acrescentou.
