text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

кукла приходит в простом пакете с фирменными бирками.
запаха никакого от неё нет.
дочке куколка нравится. уже наступил такой возврат (1,5 года) когда такие куклы уже интереснее стали, чем раньше.

доставка 3 недели. посылка отслеживалась.

.sleep!
.eat - don’t skip meals
.take time to breath .

text:
#metoo 
female employees of cure violence, a violence prevention organization formerly known as ceasefire, have accused senior administrator ricardo “cobe” williams of sexual harassment in a federal lawsuit. gary slutkin, founder and ceo of cure violence is also named as a defendant in the lawsuit, filed wednesday before a press conference.
during the conference, held at the chicago union league club, 65 w. jackson blvd., employee angalia bianca spoke about her experiences with williams.
according to bianca, in 2014 williams brought her into his office and was instructed to perform oral sex on him. after refusing, she was allowed to leave but did not file a complaint for fear of termination.
“i was hesitant to return to that room, but i felt like i had no choice,” bianca said. “i have lost 40 pounds, which my doctor has said is because of the stress from williams.”
bianca said williams tried to assault her twice more, and she almost submitted the third time but ultimately refused. williams then began to exclude bianca from work activities, retaliating against her and “ruining the work [she] loves,” bianca said.
lakisha mcgowan, another former employee, also shared her experience with williams at the press conference. according to mcgowan, while in a car with williams he began touching himself and eventually climbed on top of her before she pushed him off and told him they were both married.
mcgowan said he was dismissive of her complaints afterward and implied that if she didn’t remain silent she would lose her job.
after mcgowan filed a complaint against williams with uic, she was told that he was transitioning from a rougher life and she should not worry about it, she said at the press conference.
“as long as i kept my mouth shut, i knew my job was safe,” mcgowan said at the conference. “it was my word against [william’s], who had so much power.”

text:
i had never felt like i actually wanted to die until my kids were taken from their cribs, dramatically with police standby like i was a criminal, while i was getting served with an order that he had temporary full custody and i could only see my kids with a third party he approved of (which was of course his flying monkey sister). years of being physically abused and never saying anything, then i reacted one day and threw a piece of a 2x4 through a window that no one was near and i have my children removed. i’m not making excuses. i should have not allowed myself to react in such anger. it’s difficult, however, to not compare that one action to the years of pain he inflicted. he got me in my achilles, which ultimately led me back to him. •
•

•
•

text: glad to be back home with over ten thousand of sisters in seoul today. we’ve been condemning the prevalence of online ‘molka’ videos (secretly filming women on public toilets/transport/love motels/streets by micro spy-cams), revenge porn distribution, unfair punishments of sexual criminals and deep-rooted misogyny. even before emboldened by the global #metoo movement, we have spoken out about experience of living as a woman in a patriarchal and rapidly modernized society and sexual abuse in korea. those brave actions and voices gave me a name to unnamed senses, deeply empowered me both in my life and in my art. i feel blessed and proud to be part of this movement and my life will never be the same again. started as a tiny spark and now we’re making herstory. thank you, thank you. ✊🔥 #불편한용기 #마지막_불편한용기 #불법촬영편파수사규탄시위 #국가가_포주다 #국가가포주였다 #여자팔아세운it강국 #웹하드카르텔 #웹하드게이트 #디지털성범죄 #편파판결불법촬영규탄시위 #편파수사 #양진호게이트 #6차시위

text:
happy solstice and full moon in cancer.  it’s a perfect day to embrace the past and create the future. 
what intuitive nudges did you listen to in the last 6 months? which ones did you not?
a woman healing and embracing all of it also heals her mother.  and her daughter.  and all the women around her. 
a woman filling her own cup and stepping out into the world is the most beautiful thing there is.  because then she only chooses the people that amplify her to spend time around.  and those that want to tone her down? they fall away. 
if you’re ready to amplify your beauty your grace and your relationships sign up for my newsletter @megan.m.riley.  link in bio ❤️🌈💕🦄💗

text:
@wagggs_world @guiasdechile @agschile we're so impressed with the #16daysofactivism action that guides and scouts in chile organised! 😍😍 .
they staged a flash-mob on the streets of their capital city to demand laws to eradicate street harassment, with more than a hundred girls and boys taking part! ✊✊
.
they also handed a petition to senator yasna provoste campillay calling for the criminalisation of street harassment 👏👏 .
sarah nancollas, ceo of wagggs, said this "is a great example of how girl guides are working on the international stage to change attitudes and improve the lives of girls everywhere, which is what our movement is all about. working on projects like this also gives them the skills and the confidence to be leaders." #girlguides #girlscouts #16daysofactivism #16days #advocacy #protest #flashmob #streetharassment #speakout #metoo #timesup

text:
we want to see you're polygraph eyes

my account started like any fan account but it's quickly growing into a more powerful platform with these stronger themes- as most of you know i myself am a sexual assault survivor. 
i remember when it all went down, i felt alone. i felt alone and taboo and victimised, it was the worst feeling in the world. i wanted to cut away my very skin from my bone, as his touch still left imprints on me and it didn't help that no one my age seemed to understand.

so i've teamed up with @yungbluddominic do start up a project inspired by the song polygraph eyes by yungblud to bring awareness, so that the people like me don't have to go through that loneliness, the taboo, and all those shitty feelings.

maybe you've been assaulted, maybe you've been harrassed- maybe this is all forgein to you and all you know is that you want to support those who have been through it- please, join us. take a picture if you're polygraph eyes and use the format above. if you don't know how, just message me or @yungbluddominic and we'll help. use the hashtag #mypolygrapheyes to join. participants will be put into highlighted stories (unless they've asked not to be, of course. this is all about you and making you feel comfortable and safe.) it's wild man, you're alive- that's fuckin' crazy. you're strong, you're brilliant, you're relevant- i love you. i can't wait to see those beautiful strong polygraph eyes.

please use the hashtag #mypolygrapheyes and join us in this fight of awareness.

this is what the black hearts club looks like.
this is what the youth looks like.
🖤✊

text_retweet:
#repost @world with @get_repost
・・・
imelda cortez, a 20-year-old woman in el salvador, who was jailed with attempted murder after she gave birth to her rapist’s baby in a toilet has been freed. cortez was rushed to the hospital in april 2017 after she gave birth to a baby girl fathered by her stepfather, who has raped and sexually abused her since she was 12, in the toilet. cortez said she did not know she was pregnant, but the doctor at the hospital suspected she had tried to abort the baby and called the authorities. cortez was then arrested and handed a 20 year jail sentence after prosecutors argued that failing to tell anyone about her pregnancy or seek medical attention for the baby amounted to attempted murder under the country’s laws, which completely ban abortions. however, on monday, a court ruled that cortez had not tried to kill her child and that she was free to go home. the judge concluded that the court could not have expected her to act differently given the emotional and psychological damage inflicted by the sexual violence she had suffered since childhood. cortez was greeted by family members and supporters outside the courtroom. (📷: getty, reuters)
-

text:
anne frank was one of the most discussed jewish victims of the holocaust, she gained fame posthumously with the publication of the diary of a young girl.

text:
: #metoo: ના કહેવા બદલ કામ ગુમાવ્યું: અદિતિ રાવ હૈદરી
 અદિતિ રાવ હૈદરીએ વિશાખાપટ્ટનમમાં યોજાયેલી એક ઇવેન્ટમાં જણાવ્યું હતું કે, ‘સમાધાન’ ન કરવાના કારણે તેણે આઠ મહિના સુધી કામ ગુમાવ્યું હતું. તેણે કહ્યું હતું કે, ‘મને યાદ છે કે, મેં જ્યારે શરૂઆત કરી હતી ત્યારે હું વધારે પડતી ભોળી હતી. કેમ કે, હું પ્રોટેક્ટેડ બેકગ્રાઉન્ડમાંથી આવું છું. આવી બધી બાબતો બનતી હોવાની અફવાઓ સાચી હોવાની મને ખબર જ નહોતી. પ્રામાણિકતાથી કહું છું કે, હું ક્યારેય આવી ખરાબ ઘટનાનો ભોગ બની નથી. એક ઘટના બની હતી. જેનાથી વાસ્તવમાં મને ખાસ નુકસાન થયું નથી. જોકે, હા, મેં કામ ગુમાવ્યું હતું. કેમ કે, મને આ કરવું છે કે નહીં એવી ચોઇસ આપવામાં આવી હતી. મારા માટે એમાં વિચારવા જેવું કશું નહોતું. મારે એ છોડીને જતા રહેવું પડ્યું હતું.

 અદિતિ રાવ હૈદરીએ વિશાખાપટ્ટનમમાં યોજાયેલી એક ઇવેન્ટમાં જણાવ્યું હતું કે, ‘સમાધાન’ ન કરવાના કારણે તેણે આઠ મહિના સુધી કામ ગુમાવ્યું હતું. તેણે કહ્યું હતું કે, ‘મને યાદ છે કે, મેં જ્યારે શરૂઆત કરી હતી ત્યારે હું વધારે પડતી ભોળી હતી. કેમ કે, હું પ્રોટેક્ટેડ બેકગ્રાઉન્ડમાંથી આવું છું. આવી બધી બાબતો બનતી હોવાની અફવાઓ સાચી હોવાની મને ખબર જ નહોતી. પ્રામાણિકતાથી કહું છું કે, હું ક્યારેય આવી ખરાબ ઘટનાનો ભોગ બની નથી. એક ઘટના બની હતી. જેનાથી વાસ્તવમાં મને ખાસ નુકસાન થયું નથી. જોકે, હા, મેં કામ ગુમાવ્યું હતું. કેમ કે, મને આ કરવું છે કે નહીં એવી ચોઇસ આપવામાં આવી હતી. મારા માટે એમાં વિચારવા જેવું કશું નહોતું. મારે એ છોડીને જતા રહેવું પડ્યું હતું.

stop_filter_tweet: : ના કહેવા બદલ કામ ગુમાવ્યું : અદિતિ રાવ હૈદરી અદિતિ રાવ હૈદરીએ વિશાખાપટ્ટનમમાં યોજાયેલી એક ઇવેન્ટમાં જણાવ્યું હતું કે , ‘ સમાધાન ’ ન કરવાના કારણે તેણે આઠ મહિના સુધી કામ ગુમાવ્યું હતું . તેણે કહ્યું હતું કે , ‘ મને યાદ છે કે , મેં જ્યારે શરૂઆત કરી હતી ત્યારે હું વધારે પડતી ભોળી હતી . કેમ કે , હું પ્રોટેક્ટેડ બેકગ્રાઉન્ડમાંથી આવું છું . આવી બધી બાબતો બનતી હોવાની અફવાઓ સાચી હોવાની મને ખબર જ નહોતી . પ્રામાણિકતાથી કહું છું કે , હું ક્યારેય આવી ખરાબ ઘટનાનો ભોગ બની નથી . એક ઘટના બની હતી . જેનાથી વાસ્તવમાં મને ખાસ નુકસાન થયું નથી . જોકે , હા , મેં કામ ગુમાવ્યું હતું . કેમ કે , મને આ કરવું છે કે નહીં એવી ચોઇસ આપવામાં આવી હતી . મારા માટે એમાં વિચારવા જેવું કશું નહોતું . મારે એ છોડીને જતા રહેવું પડ્યું હતું .

text:
the irony within our generation is that as women, we ask society for consent over what we do with our bodies and seek progress in issues that are not limited to: genital mutilation, gang rape (especially against children), revenge porn, sexual assault, bride burning, honor killing, sex trafficking, child brides and so forth.

but the second a woman exercises her free will and gives her consent whether she decides to bare cleavage or willingly have sex with someone of her choice, other women will automatically deem her a ho or slut shame her.

how sad is that? in a world that is void of our permission, of our choice, of our will and of our voice.. finally being able to give consent is stigmatized and oppressed.. not by men but by our very own sisters.

if we can post pictures of our thongs and use hashtags like #thisisnotconsent and #metoo, just remember that standing up for our sisters from being put down when they utilized consent is just as, if not more powerful.

true feminism lies in changing your thought process from calling a woman who gives her consent a ho and instead calling her an example of progress. we are already marginalized enough at the hands of men so why continue the oppression at the hands of each other?

text:
skammen är inte din av anicia sundström ericsson

en bok på dikt och prosa där författaren blottar sina upplevelser, sin oro, sin längtan, sin förtvivlan - men också hur hon återvinner sitt självförtroende.

i boken tar författaren upp sina tankar om hur hon utnyttjats sexuellt. att bli förövad möjligheten att välja, förlora makten över sin kropp, att kunna säga nej! 
hon beskriver också hur hennes pappa går bort i cancer. att hon inte är beredd, inte får ta farväl, inte får hjälp att bearbeta sina känslor. 
allt som drabbar författaren ger ett ackumulerat känslomässig kaos som skapar psykisk ohälsa. detta kaos skapas av yttre faktorer - och drabbar författaren som inte har en chans att värja sig. 
boken handlar också om vägen tillbaka till bättre mående. om tron på kärleken och att våga närvara i positiva känslor. 
tack för att du delar med dig @aniciaeriksson och tack för #recex ! 🙏🏻

text: “num mundo inundado de informações irrelevantes, clareza é poder… bilhões de nós dificilmente podem se permitir o luxo de investigá-las, pois temos coisas mais urgentes a fazer, como trabalhar, tomar conta das crianças, ou cuidar dos pais idosos… isso é muito injusto, mas quem disse que a história é justa?... nossa rotina diária influencia a vida de pessoas e animais do outro lado do mundo, e alguns gestos pessoais podem inesperadamente incendiar o mundo inteiro, como aconteceu com a auto imolação de mohammed bouazizi na tunísia, que desencadeou a primavera árabe, e com as mulheres que compartilharam suas histórias de assédio sexual e deram origem ao movimento #metoo... se não criticarmos o modelo liberal não seremos capazes de corrigir suas falhas ou ir além dele.” (yuval noah harari -  21 lições para o século 21 - p. 18) #performance #contatoeimprovisação #art #beautiful #performanceart #theater #teatro #dance #martialarts #bioenergetica #grupo #grupodemovimento #lowen #piracicaba #klaussvianna

text:
it’s been 5 years since india got its sexual harassment law. but because many companies in the country still don’t completely comply with the law, it seems only natural to glorify the ones that do. however, the truth is compliance is only the beginning!
.
that’s because the current law offers protection and provision for only female victims of sexual harassment. for a prevention of sexual harassment (posh) intervention to be effective, it needs to be gender neutral and more importantly, not done only to tick a compliance check-box. it also has to ensure that each and every employee, customer and investor are aware of the organisation’s zero tolerance for sexual harassment. .
.
be.artsy uses its unique art-based programmes to help organisations prevent workplace sexual harassment. our it’s not ok campaign has already raised awareness on the topic among more than 12,000 employees. for more information, write to: shipra@be-artsy.com /akanksha@be-artsy.com. .
.

.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
final master project performance costume. 
if i am dead: he killed me :is intended to tell the story of a friend. she married a man she loved and her life descended into hell. the psychological, verbal and emotional abuse he tormented her with changed who she was fundamentally. she became what he made her into, a woman who no one would believe, listen to or help. she is left with ptsd, which is forever and keeps her from telling her story. the ptsd has scarred her permanently, and drastically effects everything. 
i share her story in memory of the girl, this woman once was, the girl who taught me how to be strong. even now as ‘damaged’ as she thinks she is, continues to teach me what true strength and the kindness of the human soul really means.

credits:
photos by emmi hyyppä
concept and realization by: dee gowans
performance by: @simonelabarga and luke biaco
choreographed by: @petalily 
produced by @agnestreplin for @lcflondon_ @unioftheartslondon 
lighting design by antony hateley
sound design by wilfred petherbridge
hair and makeup by @goshkamuah 
the most amazing technician in the world (you were right!!!): marion yarwood
thanks to: claire christie, donatella barbieri

a massive thank you to @ak liee who not only was my emotional support, but also for being my stage manager during all my chaotic rehearsals.
also thank you to @lina_aly and @oliver.to for steaming the dress for me, as well as @nashwamaatouk and oliver , for cleaning the stage of those flower petals. 
one last thank you to the amazing @julievholm , who not only had to deal with me when i was at my worst and made me laugh every chance she got, she is basically hercules. but who also helped me with many elements of testing my costume ideas and helping me sew the loops closed during the most sleep deprived hours of my life. amazing human, performer and friend.

#lcf #costume #costumedesign #performativecostume #performanceart #metoo #domesticviolence #domesticviolenceawareness #ptsdawareness #ptsd #verbalabuse #timesup #weddingdress #wedding #applique #beading

text:
cultura 'herstory', historia ilustrada del feminismo donde no cabe margaret thatcher

efe 
22/12/2018 - 8:57 am

la lucha feminista toma forma de libro en "herstory: una historia ilustrada de las mujeres", una cronología de microrrelatos y dibujos que saca a la luz hechos y protagonistas como las "soldaderas" mexicanas, pero donde no caben personajes como margaret thatcher. "cada mes podríamos añadir un tema", reconocen a efe maría basterós, cristina daura y nacho m. segarra, las autoras (en femenino porque así lo quiere el único hombre) de esta obra publicada por la editorial lumen.

el libro es un "hijo de su tiempo" gracias a la mirada actual y las ilustraciones certeras que han usado para construir este relato lleno de reivindicaciones o movimientos a favor del sufragio universal, el divorcio o el matrimonio homosexual.

en sus páginas conoceremos, por si alguien no lo sabe, que en 1910 a la revolución mexicana se incorporaron de forma activa unas mujeres llamadas "soldaderas". nos recuerdan nombres como el de feliciana enríquez de guzmán (la primera dramaturga española del siglo de oro), o nos descubren a los primeros matrimonios lésbicos en la china de principios del siglo xx. "es una elección de temas muy de ahora, queríamos que rimara con la actualidad", cuenta la también creadora de la plataforma cultural feminista quiéncoñoes, maría basterós (zaragoza, 1987), responsable de que en este libro no aparezcan mujeres como la que fuera primera ministra británica margaret thatcher.

ella, argumenta, fue la encargada de "espolear la caza de brujas del colectivo lgtb". pero un libro con perspectiva de género "no es solo sobre mujeres importantes, tiene que ser interseccional", matiza para poner de relieve que en "herstory" aparecen mujeres blancas, negras, indias, latinas o asiáticas de clase media, alta o baja, desde la prehistoria hasta el movimiento #metoo.

mujeres como la activista mexicana muxe -término que en la cultura zapoteca alude a un "tercer género" aceptado por la comunidad- amaranta gómez regalado, activista contra el sida y contra la discriminación de su colectivo.

text:
words by rebecca traister “reading the piece, i couldn’t help but think of naomi alderman’s brain-bending novel, the power, published last year. it depicts a world in which women develop the power to inflict physical pain, and to kill, via electricity that emanates from their fingers. in alderman’s fictional universe, this power is exhibited first by young women who in turn awaken it in their elders; as they are learning the possibilities and limits of their new power, the women giddily experiment with it, sending sparks and currents, determining how much of it they have, whether they can control it, and how they might best deploy it.
the book is extraordinary because it forces readers to think about all the ways — within our social, sexual, professional, and political relationships — in which men’s power over women is so much taken for granted that we don’t question it, don’t even notice it. but when women acquire an equivalent force, chaos and fear reign. the power read to many, and was regularly reviewed as, a piece of chilling dystopian fiction. but as alderman herself has said, “it’s only a dystopia for the men … nothing happens to a man in this book that is not happening right now to a woman somewhere in the world.”
•
there has historically been little cost to undercutting women of color on your way to power, because neither white women nor black men have had the power or the inclination to stand up for them in the way, for example, that crowley and his supporters are alleged to have done for jeffries in his leadership bid. and also because, hey — once you have the power, you have the power; who’s going to come for you once you ascend?..
what’s arresting is the notion that she might be in a position — might have enough swagger and sway — to imagine doing something in response. that long-powerful men like crowley might deploy a vengeful fuck-you isn’t a shocking notion … but what if newly powerful women could conceive of doing the same? it’s this very possibility that’s exhilarating for some, chilling for others: that women, and in this case, progressive women of color, newly elected in historic numbers, might team up in defense of one another, come to👇🏼

text:
transformation! 
when i was heavy i never had a goal to look good in a bikini, i thought that would never be possible so i really focused on being able to wear jeans again and feel confident 👖

i had stopped buying jeans and pants after i reached size 10 and then i just wore dresses and skirts and workout pants. i bought clothes without numbered sizes to remain in denial about how heavy i was 😥 i suppose i wore size 14 or 16 at some point but i hated buying larger sizes so i just didn't. not sure that was the best approach but it is the truth. now i know my worth isn't because i am a certain size, i don't care anymore what size i wear because i finally feel comfortable with myself.  however it's so exciting to be wearing jeans and feeling great! it's so sad i felt so horrible about myself for so long and refused to accept that alcohol made me overweight but i am so thankful for my health and wellness today 🙏

#godry #drydiet #sober #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #mentalhealth #teetotaler #sober #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #mentalhealth

text:
#barbietoo  before i left the house i made sure to dress in something loose that would not be too distracting. as i walk the streets of new york at night,one hand holds my groceries tightly, the other holds my pocket knife. i walk with urgency, my hoodie is up and my headphones in and,which are not playing music, act like a barrier between the men who catcalls and whistles at me. i see a masculine shadow at the end of the street, but i cannot see its owner. i fear it’s a man awaiting my passing. i make a detour and walk across the street. 
as i usually do on a weekend night, i was clubbing and hanging out with my girls. i normally go to gay clubs, but this weekend i went to a straight club.  once i felt a strong grip on my ass, i turned around to say what the hell, but this 6 foot tall frat guy in a polo would not look at me. this is the first time i  had my ass grabbed unsolicitedly. they have the balls to grab me, but they don’t own up to their actions. every 5 minutes i would take a headcount of my girls because the cocky boys would not listen to us when we said we did not want to grind with them. this was the first night where i saw that the boys were not listening to no. it made me wonder why they felt because it was dark and the music was loud that they could do what they want. i was not being listened to. “there is no greater threat to women than men? we’re the number one threat!” said louis c.k. in his hbo special. when are men taught to acknowledge boundaries? i should be able to leave and feel safe wherever i go without having to worry. i am tired with the way that men are treating me and other women. every women has there own story with harassment, but to tell mine i am using barbie as my proxy. when i was younger i looked up to her and she was a beacon of indepence and i vividly remember watching rapunzel barbie in my bubblegum pink room thinking “look at all that she can do for herself”. #photo #photography #art #camera #canon #fujifilm #fujitx1 #digital #digitalphoto #digitalphotography #digitalphotos #mirrorless #metoo #barbie #pink #hair #violent #ken #sexualassult

text: i like the way autumn reminds me of songs that the shadows sing as the sun sets and the monsters claim their territory. and i do realise that their crooked fingers have curled upon my heart. i haven't lost. i haven't. i have found myself. i claim my soul infront of everything that has tried to conquer it. sometimes i crumble to ashes but like a phoenix, i rise. that is my origin. i arise from darkness.

text:
as we reflect on 2018, the impact of the #metoo movement looms large. nylag has long been working with workers facing abuse, but this year many people experiencing sexual harassment in the workplace were inspired by the national conversation to come forward and seek justice. 
our client satunina was constantly harassed by her manager at a dollar store in brooklyn. now she is working with a nylag attorney to hold her employer accountable. we will fight for satunina and all survivors of sexual harassment.

text:
i am spending the weekend cleaning up my basement and decluttering, seems odd this time of year but i don't have much of a choice as my small condo sold and i need to combine the spaces! 
i found my old medical records and actually opened them, something i have avoided for years because of the pain from the miscarriages. it's so interesting to look back and see my weight over those years i was married. 
i was 142 apparently when i got married according to the medical records and when my ex h declared me too fat to love and threw me out i was 159. it's so crazy how little weight it truly was that upset him so much and my body was really put through hell with the miscarriages. for years i have hurt myself because i believed he was right, i was too fat to love. sadly after i left the pain did not go away and i stopped weighing myself when i was at 194 so i am not really sure how heavy i was. 
it's so sad that all my ex h saw in me was my body, he never saw me as anything but something for his pleasure and to give him children and quickly discarded me when i no longer suited his needs. i am so thankful to be free 🙏
#godry #drydiet #sober #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #mentalhealth #teetotaler #sober #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #mentalhealth #teetotaler #sober

text:
excited to announce a book i contributed to has been published. ➡️link in bio 
i co-authored this book with over a dozen asian leaders to address diversity issues and to create a more inclusive world. we collectively shared vulnerable and personal stories about our background, family life, history, upbringing, and what it's like growing up in the west to become the people we are today. .

with rising diversity problems in the workplace and the rise of the #metoo movement, we thought we could address what we're doing individually and collectively to address issues plaguing corporations, governments, non-profits, media, entertainment, and startups.

the authors span more than 11 cities and more than a dozen industries with varying backgrounds, spanning a couple of generations, sharing our stories to help us all progress. we hope this book inspires you further to tackle diversity and create more opportunities for inclusion.

the majority of the proceeds from book sales will support asian americans advancing justice @advancingjustice_aajc who fights for civil rights and empowers asian americans to create a more just america for all
.
.
.
.
.

eco-cycle

.
enormous gratitude to bohemian foundation for making this possible.
greg schochet on tele, damon smith on drums.

text:
abuse. abuse of power, abuse of people, abuse of humanity. this cycle is a continuous foreboding one that permeates through society. that same man that gave the convicted rapist a ‘6 month jail term’ (brock turner) is the same man who raped a woman years ago. and she stayed silent because she knew the people in power were the ones who had committed the crime previously or were benefitting from this cycle so saw no needs to change it, like white privilege, male privilege, etc. just like now when brock turner grows up and he may be put into a position of power because we can’t let ‘20 minutes of action’ destroy his future (his father said that). but no one seems to bother about the survivors story or their life. he had a choice to ‘ruin’ his life, she didn’t. so why does he get the sympathy vote. this cycle of abuse continues due to capitalism, brock turner is very rich, he may find himself at the top of a powerful chain one day, we all know rape accusations and even convictions don’t ruin a perpetrator’s life (trump, kavanaugh), and he will be making the rules for the future hims/her. sexual assault does not discriminate. we need to make our voices heard, for the survivors who did not survive, for the survivors who are speaking up but are not being heard, for the survivors who are silent in this ghastly world which treats them like rubbish. whenever something like this happens and it makes the news, call your mp’s, person of representative tell them your thoughts and opinions and what you want them to do. regardless if you voted for them or not, make a difference. we all can.

text:
#10daysofgratitude
.
day 1: we are ready for 2019! 2018 has been a year of growth at @aapiwomenlead. today we express so much gratitude and appreciation for all of the volunteers and members who joined aapiwl's #imready movement. in 2018, we were only at the very beginning with super limited resources. we are now building and building. thank you to everyone at @usow for hosting this amazing conference of womxn. this is where we had 80 attendees wait in line to take our survey on asian and pacific islander womxn’s experiences with violence. we look forward to the growth of this movement! the #imready movement consists of urban planners, teachers, techies, students, academics, survivors, lawyers, artists, politicians, activists, founders, chefs, business owners, and moms and soooo much more from all over the nation. thank you for sharing your brilliance, expertise, criticisms, curiosities and stories with us. please know we see you, hear you and absolutely appreciate you. enjoy these snap shots of some of the people who have made this all possible. ❤️ aapi women lead
.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

the guardian

text:
well i can wash out forty four pairs of socks
and have 'em on the line.
you know i can starch and iron two dozen shirts
'fore you can count from one to nine.
i can slip up a great big dip up of lard
from a drippings can.
throw it in the skillet, do my shopping,
and be back before it melts in the pan. 'cause i'm a woman...
w-o-m-a-n.
let me tell ya again.
i'm a woman...
w-o-m-a-n.

well i can rub and scrub
'til this house shines just like a dime.
feed the baby, grease the car,
powder my nose at the same time.
you know i can get all dressed up,
go out swinging with the m-a-n,
jump in bed at five, sleep 'til 6,
and start all over again.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
wishing you all a joyous holiday with family and friends❤️🎄❤️thank you for your support and kindness throughout the past year🙏thanks to those who purchased, read, and reviewed my novel😍📘🥂as an indie published author, i rely on good old grass roots marketing to help spread the word about this poignant, timely story.
here is an excerpt from the most recent review by book blogger, leonard tillerman.
⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
“i found the plot of this novel to be absolutely captivating and engaging. as a reader you will simply melt right into this book.  it is all about the strength of the human spirit against what seem to be impossible odds.  although i can personally identify and connect with prue’s childhood and the trauma she experienced, such a personal connection is not needed to love this book. you just have to be human.  the writing flows beautifully and alternates between the past and present in an entirely seamless fashion.  to say i consider this novel to be compelling and enthralling would be a drastic understatement.  in truth, i found it to be magical and it moved me deeply.”
•
•
•
•
•

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
this is an open call for submissions. we are here to unite the community of #survivors, allies, advocates, educators, legislators and supporters. we are here to take #metoo one step further. to collect and share your experiences in any way that you want to express them create a culture of honesty, #empowerment, and safety in numbers. share your story anonymously, without fear of judgement or retribution. we are here to bring together the many voices of the movement to #endrape culture, to end gender-based discrimination and bias, to turn our knowledge into real change to a culture of #consent and #equity. for ourselves, as we continue to understand the system we live in and how to move on from our trauma. for our children, so that they may grow up in a world of respect and #empathy that for so long we have lived without. #linkinbio to find out more about our nonprofit's mission. #donate during this season of giving so that we have the resources to give back to all of you. building a company, a #community web platform, and aligning with other #activists and nonprofits that #share our passion. thank you to our #followers for all of the kind messages and our donors for believing in us so far. we appreciate you. we love you. we believe you.

text:
elimination of violence against women

edo state government is keen on protecting women and girls hence the event, elimination of violence against women 2018, #hearmetoo organized by the commissioner for women affairs and social development, hon. (mrs.) magdalene ohehen at eguare primary school, oria community in esan south-east lga of edo state on friday the 21st of december, 2018.

local government chairperson's and women across the three senatorial districts in the state graced the occasion with their presence as the guest speaker, amb. chief (mrs.) kadiri ezolome encouraged the women to always speak out against all forms of violence meted on them.

building on the momentum of global movements and grassroots campaigns such as ‘#metoo’, “#timesup”, “#balancetonporc” “#niunamenos”, #metooindia and “hollaback!”, the un theme for this year’s 16 days of activism against gender-based violence (25 november – 10 december) under the unite to end violence against women campaign is, orange the world: #hearmetoo.

violence against women and girls is a grave violation of human rights. its impact ranges from immediate to long-term multiple physical, sexual and mental consequences for women and girls, including death. it negatively affects women’s general well-being and prevents women from fully participating in society. violence not only has negative consequences for women but also their families, the community and the country at large.

speak up, it's time to take action.

https://m.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=301343013830535&id=135003433797828

text:
everyone has a role to play in preventing sexual assault. there are many different ways that you can step in or make a difference if you see someone at risk. you can be a bystander.
i joined women affairs and poverty alleviation to walk against sexual violence. we can no longer keep mute on this matter, through  the fact she is your wife/husband or girlfriend/ boyfriend or fiancée/fiancé doesn't give you the right to violate her sexual right.consent is very important.
no is no and yes is yes,it should be an agreement.just because you bought someone  dinner or a drink, doesn't mean that they owe them sex in return, you gave willingly, you weren't compelled to do it. if you can't afford the dinner don't buy it, it is not by force.

sexual violence is an offence. without consent, it is sexual assault. 
#dfathersprincess #metoo #sexedu #dsvrt #wapa #pieceofmyheartfoundation

text:
sophie kahn, machines for suffering i, 2018, life size 3d print (laser-sintered nylon) from 3d laser scan, with gesso and acrylic paint. on display in the exhibition transfigured at c24 gallery from january 11 - february 23, 2018
_______________
at its most fundamental level, machines for suffering i can be considered a sculptural ode to hysteria patients of the past. countless women whose behavior was outside the socially accepted norm were pathologized and institutionalized. they were treated at the hands of doctors who used newly developing photographic technology to document voyeuristic staged scenes of hysterical women in the throes of insanity. 
_______________
working from a background in photography and art history, kahn’s post-photographic work sets her in dialogue with the history of medical photography and its impact on the development of photographic technology. her interest in exposing the way technology fails to capture life starkly contrasts with the 19th century belief that photography was a means of capturing and presenting a “medical truth.”
_______________ 
the series title alludes to the poignant statement by pablo picasso, made to his mistress françoise gilot: “women are machines for suffering.” the series offers an equally potent exposition of the production and consumption of female anguish, especially relevant in the time of the #metoo movement.
.

text:
"eu morro de agonia quando penso nas mulheres tendo que escolher roupas, onde ficar, como sentar, medo da hora de chegar em casa (eu também tenho mas podem me roubar o material... das mulheres roubam a liberdade e a dignidade). sou filho único e irmão de três mulheres, esposo e pai de uma menina, a crio para ser forte, autônoma e resistente ao mundo mas, ele está cada vez mais opressor e ela é um poço de ternura. tenho medo desse mundo.  acredito que seja obrigação de cada um trabalhar pra construir um mundo melhor de igualdade e oportunidade. uma mulher não pode ser impedida de realizar algo por ser mulher, é preciso abrir mentes, criar oportunidades e rever conceitos pra trazer a igualdade pra cada um de nós!"
.
relato de paulo sergio rufino freire, 42 anos, brasília/df
.

text:
idioten stötte på mig på en sexfest när jag satt i ett hörn i köket och ritade. jag deltog inte, jag var tillbakadragen, han tyckte mina ögon "såg ut att vilja förstå" and the rest wasn't just history, it was abuse.

fan ta personer som söker upp de ängsligaste och använder tekniker för att vinna deras förtroende och sen använder dem som emotional och/eller sexual punchingbags.

jag kommer alltid känna ett ansvar att ingen blir behandlad av honom som han behandlade mig, jag har gjort vad jag kunnat för det. till viss del måste jag också få/kunna lägga det bakom mig eftersom han är en fjärt i universum och jag inte kan ta det ansvaret att informera omgivningen och potentiella offer längre än jag redan gjort.

ilizas humor är cisbinär, tyvärr, men detta she said well.

#metoo #selfcare #sexualpredators #abuse #frihet

text:
i got a new hairdo!🤘🏼
a long over due decision. new colour & hair style = priceless.
i'm not ready yet to talk publicly about the traumatic event that happened to me 4 years ago (on the night of dec 26th-27th) that broke me...but i can say that this new hair style will help me heal. 👀💇🏻
i'm starting to write a documentary 🎥on the relation we have with our hair and our self esteem...thank you @mateomat and your @sanstabouproductioncompany for accepting my self healing project.🙏🏼❤️
.
.
j'ai une nouvelle tête!🤘🏼
une décision qui était plus que dû. car, une nouvelle couleur et coupe de cheveux = ça n'a pas de prix.
je ne suis pas encore prête de parler publiquement de l'événement traumatisant qui m'est arrivé il y a 4 ans (la nuit du 26-27 décembre) qui m'a complètement brisée...mais je peux dire que ce changement de tête va m'aider à me reconstruire. 👀💇🏻
je commence à écrire un documentaire 🎥 sur la relation que nous entretenons avec nos cheveux et notre estime de soi... merci à @mateomat et sa boîte de production @sanstabouproductiond'accepter mon projet qui me guérira. 🙏🏼❤️

text:
i have traveled from one side of the country to the other and i found the real santa in the place of my birth, worcester. (actually shrewsbury)

if you love me or santa, go buy the cheapest gas around at the world's best truck stop and get breakfast at the world's greatest diner across the street.  then buy lions club calendars, raffles and tip like you are king lebron james in cleveland.

i used to take my sister to eat here when we were studying at wpi and fitchburg state.  my other sisters and i used to come and buy blunt raps, oj to mix with vodka and then we used to date rape the hell out of each other out behind mr wachusset or at the edgemere drive in.  this was in the ancient past before marty, deval, mitt, baker, scott brown,  susan warren, all the other bullies, rich white men and #metoo took the fun out of everything.

the kicker is that my favorite commedian has eaten at the diner... i never name names, but let's just say it is not the guy who thinks it's funny to make jokes about an immigrant with mental health issues that just wants to sell soup or boots.  the worst tinder date i ever had ended when i stood up for him... that chick was crazy

#makedatagreatagain
#therealsanta
#hessweatinghisassoff
#itstoocoldforthis

text:
hey folks! 🤶

i´ve always liked the melody of eartha kitt´s song "santa baby" but never felt related to the lyrics. thank god @mileycyrus performed an updated feminist version of the song on @fallontonight .
she´s taking a stance for equal rights and against sexism.
singing this version is much more fun and has really struck a chord with me!
have a closer look at the lyrics down below if you are interested
enjoy my angry and sassy cover version! 😁 "santa baby, i hear you got some presents for me
miley (or "nicky" in this case... 😜), i've been an awfully good girl
santa baby, so hurry down the chimney tonight

santa baby, i don't need any fancy jewelry
not me, i've got something else in mind
santa baby, and i don't need your presents tonight

don't want diamonds, cash, or stars
nothing that comes in a box
no more fluff, i've had enough
and i can buy my own damn stuff

santa baby, i´ve got a baller car of my own
no loan, i bought it all by myself
santa baby, with zero help from elf on a shelf

listen santa to what i say
a girl's best friend is an equal pay
so stop interrupting me when i talk
and don't text me pictures of your... santa baby, i'd love to know my ass won't get grabbed
at work by some ignorant jerk
tell the dirtbag to put away the chimney tonight
put away the chimney tonight
just put away your chimney tonight
just put away your chimney tonight"

text:
ever shape shifting
reaching, stealing 
the latest glory
to wear and call your own

a glimmer that attracts 
blind followers
then fades 
here comes the need of new
whatever cost
whatever form
to feed and cover 
you, you, and you

toss and cheat
steal and sneak
to get what brings 
your desired “light”

don’t look around
don’t look behind
at the debris
the wounded
the fallen 
from your deceptive and corrupt
hollow and treacherous
pharisaic pursuits //// please know that what i write is true. it is from me experience of deep darkness and deceit and abuse. of wolves in sheeps clothing. it’s not easy to write and share most times because i'm a pharisee too. i don't want to write so much that it speaks in ways that separate me from the same continual  need of mercy, forgiveness, and grace.... because that would not be true.

text:
*всему свое время*
мы порой чего-то так сильно хотим, что трудно заснуть ночью, сосредоточиться на работе, расслабиться и принять то, что есть!
проходит время и ты устаешь ждааать и меняешь фокус своего внимания на другую цель / желание / предмет. 
и начинаешь увлекаться совсем другим процессом, как вдруг бабаах!!!💣💥
то, что ты так сильно хотел, ждал... вот оно! подарок судьбы, чудо! и ты уже воспринимаешь это спокойно, на душе тихая радость и благодарность. и только потом понимаешь, что это надо было именно сейчас. тогда ты был не готов!
не стоит торопить события, "дедушка мороз" сам знает, когда подарить вам подарок. 
расслабьтесь, займитесь пока другим делом, иначе можно прождать годами..
ведь в мире столько прекрасного, чем можно себя увлечь...) добрых мыслей вам на ночь. 
#мысли #философия #размышления #смысл #фокусвнимания #жизнь #цели #мотивация #душа #тг #мысливслух #тг_бубнова #благодарность #благо #soul #metoo #life

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn
